21.
 
Multiple Unit Franchise Agreement Contingency
.
Seller and Purchaser acknowledge that they have entered into this Contract to transfer title to the Real Estate so that Purchaser can operate the Restaurant located thereon as a franchisee of Seller pursuant to that Multiple Unit Franchise Agreement ("MUFA") of even date herewith. The parties further acknowledge that if the MUFA is terminated, for any reason, before the consummation of the transaction contemplated herein, this Contract shall terminate immediately and the Earnest Money shall be immediately returned to Purchaser, except if the MUFA is terminated before the consummation of the transaction contemplated herein because of Purchaser breach thereof, in which event the Seller shall be entitled to retain the Earnest Money as liquidated damages.
22.
 
