The Trustee may appoint an authenticating agent acceptable to the Company to authenticate Debentures.  An authenticating agent may authenticate Debentures whenever the Trustee may do so.  Each reference in this Indenture to authentication by the Trustee includes authentication by such agent.  An authenticating agent has the same rights as an Agent to deal with the Company or an Affiliate.
 
