.  A "Legal Holiday" is a Saturday, a Sunday or a day on which the Trustee or banking institutions generally are not required to be open.  If a payment date is a Legal Holiday at a place of payment, payment may be made at that place on the next succeeding day that is not a Legal Holiday, and no interest shall accrue for the intervening period.
