in all cases, whether or not caused or arising, in whole or in part, out of the comparative, contributory or sole negligence of any agent or related person
provided
 
  No Affiliate of an Agent or a Lender that obtains the benefits of any Collateral by virtue of the provisions hereof or of any Security Document shall have any right to notice of any action or to consent to, direct or object to any action hereunder or under any other Loan Document or otherwise in respect of the Collateral (including the release or impairment of any Collateral) other than in its capacity as a Lender and, in such case, only to the extent expressly provided in the Loan Documents.  Notwithstanding any other provision of this Article IX to the contrary, the Administrative Agent shall not be required to verify the payment of, or that other satisfactory arrangements have been made with respect to, Hedge Agreements secured by the Security Documents and treasury, depository and cash management services or automated clearinghouse transfer of funds and commercial credit card, stored value card and merchant card services secured by the Security Documents, unless the Administrative Agent has received written notice of such agreements or services, together with such supporting documentation as the Administrative Agent may request.
